    "causal_summary": "Per-feature snippet files in feature catalogs and manual testing playbooks carry a globally sequential numeric prefix (`001-feature-name.md`, `NNN-feature-name.md`) that \"continues across categories and does not reset.\" That prefix makes the packages hard to maintain: inserting, reordering, or moving a feature forces a renumber, the global sequence drifts (real folders already mix `007` next to `024`), and two features can only be told apart by their number — producing duplicate slugs once the number is stripped",
